I 💖 SASHA COLBY you best believe I am Team Hawaii this season of #DragRace 🤩

Years ago Sasha and I met backstage getting ready to perform at Bushwig and the most immediate thing about her is her kind loving maternal energy. Her presence even off stage radiates like the sun— warm, comforting, joyful ☀️

We are both from the same Hawaiian island (but opposite neighborhoods) and close in age to have been going to high school at the same time. We are both from a generation and Bible culture where you don’t talk about queerness and to be visibly different is uncomfortable. To see her make it off the island and fully be who she is, is an inspiration to me and huge life motivation ❤️ Aloha nui loa a pomaika’i, tita! #TeamSasha @sashacolby 🌺🌴🏳️‍⚧️✨👑

Cotton candy act self-portrait 🎨🍬 

Last Saturday was my “comeback” show, my first public performance since John’s hospice and passing. It was very comforting to do it with my beloved @aplusdragshow gayasian nightlife family and y’all I felt powerful af— during Asian American Pacific Islander History Month and at THE Brooklyn Museum in a packed 400 person theater???! 🤯 

To gradually pick up my “old” pre-🦠 life back again after so much debilitating grief is confusing, exhilarating, terrifying, and joyful all at once. BUT I AM HERE FOR IT BABAYYYY 😎 #LFG 💪💖

🎥: @brooklynmuseum @lindafelcher

Even though I am from Oahu, the island of Maui is still Hawaii and our community. I have loving memories of Lahaina with my family and it is so shocking to see it gone 💔

I BROKE MY FOOT 🥲🦶💔

Super bummed to announce I have to pull out of my September and October shows (I didn’t book for November yet so who knows what is beyond). Obviously I cannot dance until I am fully healed 😭

On the day of my accident, the hospital said there was no fracture and sent me away. Then days later, still in pain and my foot increasingly turning into a purple potato, I went to a podiatrist for more imaging and it is indeed actually fractured. Always listen to your body and intuition and get a second opinion if something doesn’t feel right.

I’m in a cast and boot but I’ll be ok and will be resting for a while (aka lots of rhinestoning to come lol)

sigh k bye 🤷🏻‍♀️🙋🏻‍♀️✨

Rhinestoned crustacean headdress made by me! I took an unfinished abandoned shrimp costume from 6 years ago and turned it into a glamour lobster head 👸🏻🦞✨

I was supposed to be in my home state Hawaii right now but I’m making the best of my grounded broken foot time by going to the annual NYC dog parade instead. We took John’s beloved dog Parker and we dressed as a family of lobsters!

John, a Maine native, was a proud lobster snob because he grew up with a fisherman father. His favorite holiday was Halloween too. If last year was any indicator, I start to slip into my feels the steepest around this time because I miss his excitement and enthusiasm. It was nice and comforting to celebrate all his favorite things in a fun event 🥳

I am still bracing for the holidays to be tough but as time goes on I learn more about how coping with grief doesn’t have to always be somber and serious— it is equally valid to laugh, be silly, and party as a way to continue loving someone. If joy was the product together in life, it only makes sense to keep doing joyful things beyond life in order to still feel together 💝🙏

💃🏻 SHOW ANNOUNCEMENT + BROKEN FOOT UPDATE:

I’ve been out of my cast since Halloween, doing physical therapy rehabilitating the ligaments, and occasionally still walking with a cane.

My doctor cleared me to perform starting January so I took it as literal as possible— I’m performing at Red Pavilion @redpavilionbk for the Shanghai Foxtrot NYE soirée! Literally January 1 at the stroke of midnight! 😆🥳

Buy tickets NOW before it sells out! Tix 🎟️ link iん  my 🅱️i⭕️

I’m both sad and mad I have to write another one of these and especially around the holidays. Of course I’d like my page to be curated happy sexy fun content all the time but that wouldn’t be human nor realistic.

I’m currently out of the country and woke up in my hotel bed to the news. It took me days to write out my thoughts and marinate in memories as it kept sinking in and it still is. Idk if I can write more publicly.

(Note: I don’t have access to phone service yet so I won’t be able to answer SMS texts or receive calls)

These pics are an extension of my last post because I could not fit them all 🙏

I’ve had little soft cries every morning reading all the kindhearted messages of condolences and your own sweet (mostly hilarious) memories of Qing.

Yesterday I went shopping and saw designer perfume. I remember Qing’s two go to perfumes was Marc Jacobs Daisy for school/work/shopping and Versace Yellow Diamond for partying/dates.

Those who know me know that I fall asleep and wake up very inconsistently. Before even looking at the clock, if the apartment was empty I could tell where she went based on what I could smell. At the department store yesterday I saw both of these perfumes. I sniffed both of them hoping to time travel and revisit an old place the way only scent does. I didn’t know what I was going to feel but surprisingly it wasn’t sad! Despite all the rush and clamoring of shoppers and Christmas music, that sensory transport felt peaceful, like a gentle warm loving hug in a quiet place ❤️☺️
